---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="ChatGPT Privacy Protection: How to Mask PII Before Sending to OpenAI"
  description="Protect your privacy when using ChatGPT. Learn how to mask phone numbers, emails, and personal data before they reach OpenAI's servers. Set up a local privacy proxy in 30 seconds."
  keywords="ChatGPT隐私保护,防止ChatGPT数据泄露,OpenAI数据安全,PII脱敏ChatGPT,聊天数据隐私保护"
  canonicalURL="https://privacygw.pages.dev/protect-chatgpt-privacy"
  ogType="article">
  <Nav />

  <section class="seo-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="seo-header">
        <div class="seo-badge">ChatGPT Privacy Guide</div>
        <h1>ChatGPT Privacy Protection: Mask PII Before Sending to OpenAI</h1>
        <p class="seo-subtitle">
          Every time you paste customer data, personal information, or business documents into
          ChatGPT, that data is processed on OpenAI's servers. Here is how to use AI Privacy Gateway
          to automatically mask sensitive information before it ever reaches ChatGPT.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="seo-tldr glass">
        <strong>TL;DR:</strong> Set up AI Privacy Gateway as a local proxy and configure any
        OpenAI-compatible client app to route through it. ChatGPT desktop, API clients, and
        third-party apps all get PII-protected. Takes 30 seconds.
      </div>

      <h2>Why ChatGPT Needs Privacy Protection</h2>
      <p>
        ChatGPT processes billions of conversations daily. While OpenAI has privacy and data usage
        controls, the fundamental architecture means your data is processed on their servers.
        Consider these risks:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Training data leakage:</strong> Data you share could be used for model training unless you opt out</li>
        <li><strong>Data breach surface:</strong> Your prompts travel across the internet to OpenAI's servers</li>
        <li><strong>Inadvertent sharing:</strong> Easy to accidentally paste PII or confidential data in a prompt</li>
        <li><strong>Team/enterprise settings:</strong> Even in enterprise, your data transits through OpenAI's infrastructure</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        A local privacy proxy is the most effective way to ensure sensitive data never reaches
        OpenAI's servers in readable form.
      </p>

      <h2>How AI Privacy Gateway Protects ChatGPT</h2>
      <p>
        The gateway acts as a transparent proxy between your ChatGPT client and OpenAI's API.
        It intercepts every API call, scans for PII patterns, and replaces sensitive data with
        safe placeholders before forwarding to OpenAI.
      </p>

      <div class="diagram-flow glass">
        <div class="diagram-row">
          <div class="diagram-node">ChatGPT Client</div>
          <div class="diagram-arrow">&rarr;</div>
          <div class="diagram-node diagram-accent">Privacy Gateway</div>
          <div class="diagram-arrow">&rarr;</div>
          <div class="diagram-node diagram-alt">OpenAI API</div>
        </div>
        <div class="diagram-note">PII is masked by the gateway before reaching OpenAI</div>
      </div>

      <h2>Setup Guide: Privacy-Protect Your ChatGPT Usage</h2>

      <h3>Step 1: Install the Gateway</h3>

      <div class="code-block glass">
        <div class="code-block-title">Docker (recommended)</div>
        <pre><code>docker run -d \
  --name ai-privacy-gw \
  -p 9999:9999 \
  -v ./vault_data:/app/vault_data \
  -e TARGET_LLM=https://api.openai.com \
  ghcr.io/gunxueqiu6/ai-privacy-gateway:lite</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h3>Step 2: Route Your API Calls Through the Gateway</h3>
      <p>If you use ChatGPT via API (OpenAI SDK, LangChain, or any library):</p>

      <div class="code-block glass">
        <div class="code-block-title">Python OpenAI SDK</div>
        <pre><code>from openai import OpenAI

client = OpenAI(
    base_url="http://localhost:9999/v1",  # Route through privacy gateway
    api_key="sk-..."                       # Your original key still works
)

# All PII in your prompts is now automatically masked
response = client.chat.completions.create(
    model="gpt-4",
    messages=[&#123;"role": "user", "content": "My phone is 13812345678 and email is alice@example.com"&#125;]
)</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h3>Step 3: Use the ChatGPT Privacy Browser</h3>
      <p>
        For web-based ChatGPT usage, use the <strong>AI Privacy Gateway browser extension</strong>
        that intercepts requests from chat.openai.com and routes them through your local gateway.
        Download it from the <a href="/download">download page</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>What PII Gets Masked in ChatGPT</h2>
      <div class="entity-grid">
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-phone">Phone</span> +86 13812345678 → [PHONE_1]</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-email">Email</span> alice@example.com → [EMAIL_1]</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-id">ID Card</span> 110101199001011234 → [IDCARD_1]</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-bank">Bank</span> 6222021234567890 → [BANKCARD_1]</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-name">Name</span> 张三 → [PER_1]</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-loc">Address</span> 北京市海淀区 → [LOC_1]</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-org">Company</span> 科技有限公司 → [ORG_1]</div>
        <div class="entity-item"><span class="entity-chip chip-secret">Custom</span> API keys, passwords → user-defined</div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <div class="seo-faq glass" id="faq">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Does this work with ChatGPT Plus or Team plans?</h3>
          <p>Yes. The gateway works with any OpenAI plan. It intercepts API calls regardless of your subscription tier.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can I use it with ChatGPT's web interface?</h3>
          <p>Yes, using the browser extension. The extension intercepts requests from chat.openai.com and routes them through your local gateway. Download it from the download page.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Does the gateway store my data?</h3>
          <p>No. The gateway does not store your prompts or responses. The masking mapping is stored locally in an encrypted SQLite vault that never leaves your machine.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Will it affect ChatGPT's response quality?</h3>
          <p>No. ChatGPT responds to the masked content with placeholders. The gateway then restores the original values in the response before returning it to you. You see the complete, unmasked response.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Is this better than just being careful about what I paste?</h3>
          <p>Yes. Human error is the biggest privacy risk. The gateway catches sensitive data you might not notice — like embedded phone numbers in code samples, email addresses in configuration files, or ID numbers in test data.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="seo-cta">
        <h2>Protect Your ChatGPT Conversations</h2>
        <p>Deploy AI Privacy Gateway in 30 seconds. No code changes needed.</p>
        <div class="seo-cta-buttons">
          <a href="/download" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Get Started Free</a>
          <a href="/demo" class="btn btn-ghost btn-lg">Try the Demo</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ Schema -->
      <script type="application/ld+json">{
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "FAQPage",
        "mainEntity": [
          { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does this work with ChatGPT Plus or Team plans?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. Works with any OpenAI plan." } },
          { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does the gateway store my data?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. The gateway does not store prompts or responses. Mapping data stays local." } },
          { "@type": "Question", "name": "Will it affect ChatGPT's response quality?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "No. ChatGPT sees masked placeholders; the gateway restores original values in responses." } }
        ]
      }</script>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .seo-page { padding: 8rem 0 4rem; }
  .seo-page .container { max-width: 820px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .seo-header { margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .seo-badge {
    display: inline-block; padding: 0.35rem 0.85rem; border-radius: 20px;
    font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--primary);
    background: rgba(134, 239, 172, 0.08); border: 1px solid rgba(134, 239, 172, 0.15);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .seo-page h1 { font-size: 2.75rem; font-weight: 800; letter-spacing: -0.04em; line-height: 1.15; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .seo-subtitle { font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8; }
  .seo-tldr { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.7; color: var(--text-primary); }
  .seo-tldr strong { color: var(--primary); }
  .seo-tldr code { background: var(--bg-deep); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }
  .seo-page h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: -0.03em; margin: 3rem 0 1rem; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .seo-page h3 { font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 600; margin: 2rem 0 0.75rem; }
  .seo-page p { color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .seo-page ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .seo-page ul li { padding: 0.5rem 0 0.5rem 1.5rem; position: relative; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; }
  .seo-page ul li::before { content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0.9rem; width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--primary); opacity: 0.5; }
  .seo-page a { color: var(--primary); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }
  .seo-page a:hover { color: var(--accent); }
  .code-block { padding: 1.25rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .code-block-title { font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }
  .code-block pre { margin: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; line-height: 1.7; overflow-x: auto; }
  .code-block code { color: var(--primary); font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; }
  .diagram-flow { padding: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .diagram-row { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .diagram-node { padding: 0.6rem 1.25rem; border-radius: 10px; font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; background: rgba(134, 239, 172, 0.06); border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--primary); }
  .diagram-accent { color: var(--accent); background: rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.06); }
  .diagram-alt { color: var(--warning); background: rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.06); }
  .diagram-arrow { font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--text-muted); }
  .diagram-note { text-align: center; font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text-muted); font-style: italic; }
  .entity-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .entity-item { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.75rem; font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.5; }
  .entity-chip { font-size: 0.7rem; font-weight: 600; padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem; border-radius: 4px; white-space: nowrap; }
  .chip-secret { background: rgba(248, 113, 113, 0.12); color: #f87171; }
  .chip-phone { background: rgba(251, 191, 36, 0.12); color: #fbbf24; }
  .chip-email { background: rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.12); color: #60a5fa; }
  .chip-id { background: rgba(134, 239, 172, 0.12); color: #86efac; }
  .chip-bank { background: rgba(244, 114, 182, 0.12); color: #f472b6; }
  .chip-name { background: rgba(167, 139, 250, 0.12); color: #a78bfa; }
  .chip-loc { background: rgba(252, 165, 165, 0.12); color: #fca5a5; }
  .chip-org { background: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.12); color: #94a3b8; }
  .seo-faq { padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 3rem; }
  .seo-faq h2 { border: none; margin-top: 0; }
  .faq-item { padding: 1rem 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .faq-item:last-child { border: none; }
  .faq-item h3 { margin: 0 0 0.5rem; font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--text-primary); }
  .faq-item p { margin: 0; font-size: 0.92rem; }
  .seo-cta { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 2rem; background: var(--glass-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 20px; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .seo-cta h2 { margin-top: 0; border: none; }
  .seo-cta p { color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .seo-cta-buttons { display: flex; gap: 1rem; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .seo-page { padding: 6rem 0 3rem; }
    .seo-page h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
    .seo-page h2 { font-size: 1.4rem; }
    .entity-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .diagram-row { flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }
  }
  @media (max-width: 639px) {
    .seo-page h1 { font-size: 1.75rem; }
    .seo-cta-buttons { flex-direction: column; }
    .seo-cta-buttons .btn { width: 100%; }
  }
</style>
